      "date": "2013-02-12 21:19:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nJinshan, I was talking to Brian a bit about this issue, and we're not convinced the list of cached env's is necessary at all. Why can't we simply allocate and free a cl_env structure directly from the SLAB cache each time it's needed (i.e. http://review.whamcloud.com/5204)? This extra layer of caching seems redundant and completely unnecessary without more investigation.",
